The '''Council for the Defense of Historical, Archaeological, Artistic and Tourist Heritage''' ({{lang-pt|Conselho de Defesa do Patrimônio Histórico, Arqueológico, Artístico e Turístico}}), or '''CONDEPHAAT''', protects, values and communicates information about cultural heritage in the [[State of São Paulo]], Brazil. This includes monuments, buildings, natural areas, and historical areas, amongst other things. The Council was started in 1968. It is linked with SEC-SP.<ref name="cultura" />

