'''Henry Alan Lawson Skinner''' born  [[Erin, Ontario]] on September 26, 1899 <ref name="Who's Who">{{cite book |author1=Roberts,Charles George Douglas |author2=Tunnell, Arthur L. |title=The Canadian Who's Who |publisher=University of Toronto Press|location=|year=1960 |pages=1026 |isbn=|oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>  was a [[Canadians|Canadian]] anatomist and classical scholar<ref name="Meanings">{{cite book |author=Haubrich, William S. |title=Medical Meanings: A Glossary of Word Origins, Second Edition |publisher=American College of Physicians |location=Philadelphia, Pa |year=2003 |pages=vii |isbn=1-930513-49-6 |oclc= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8xCRO8ORO0EC&pg=PP13&vq=Skinner&dq=%22Henry+alan+Skinner%22+ |accessdate=}}</ref> who wrote ''The Origin of Medical Terms'', published by The Williams & Wilkins Company, Baltimore in 1949. He received his M.B from Toronto,<ref name=" Faculty of Medicine">{{cite book |author= University of Western Ontario Faculty of Medicine |title=Announcement |publisher=University of Western Ontario |location=|year=1963|pages=|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=PaJNAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Henry+Alan+Skinner%22&dq=%22Henry+Alan+Skinner%22 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref> and was appointed assistant professor of Anatomy at the [[University of Western Ontario]] in 1929.<ref name="Science">{{cite journal |author= H B Ward  |title=Maintaining the Standards and the Scientific Usefulness of the National Parks (announcement) |journal = [[Science (journal)|Science]] | date=January 4, 1929 |volume =69 |issue=1775 |pages=14–5 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h60PAAAAIAAJ&q=%22Henry+Alan+Skinner%22&dq=%22Henry+Alan+Skinner%22|oclc= |doi=10.1126/science.69.1775.14 |accessdate= |pmid= 17840450}}</ref>  By 1963 he had risen to Professor and Head of the Department of Anatomy at Western Ontario.<ref name=" Faculty of Medicine"/>

