{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox person | name = Rebekka Armstrong | image = | image_size = 150px | caption = | birth_name = Rebekka Lynn Armstrong | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1967|2|20|mf=y}} | birth_place = [[Bakersfield, California]], U.S.<ref name=wekinglypigs>{{cite web|url=http://wekinglypigs.com/cgi-bin/nand/search/pmstat?browse=%3A%3ACONFIG%3A%3Amodelbrowse&key=armstrong%2C+rebekka+lynn&limit=0|title=Rebekka Armstrong|accessdate=7 July 2015}}</ref> | nationality = American | occupation = model, bodybuilder | module = {{Infobox Playboy Playmate | embed = yes | name = <!-- leave blank --> | issue = September 1986 | preceded = [[Ava Fabian]] | succeeded = [[Katherine Hushaw]] | bust = 34" | waist = 23" | hips = 32" | height = {{height|ft=5|in=7}} | weight = {{convert|110|lb|kg st|abbr=on}} }} }}
'''Rebekka Lynn Armstrong''' is an American [[HIV|HIV/AIDs]] activist and former model and bodybuilder. She was ''Playboy'' [[Playboy Playmate|Playmate of the Month]] for September 1986. Eight years later, she was the first Playmate to publicly announce that she is HIV-positive.
==Biography== Armstrong announced that she is HIV-positive in the September 1994 issue of ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]''. She said that she had known she was infected since 1989, but spent two years after her diagnosis escaping into substance abuse. By the time of the publication of ''The Advocate'' article, she had come out as a [[lesbian]] and decided to educate others about HIV/AIDS, especially among lesbian and [[bisexuality|bisexual]] women. She said she was unsure of when she had contracted the virus, but might have as early as age 16.<ref name=Kort940906>{{cite journal |last=Kort |first=Michele |date=September 6, 1994 |title=Portrait of a Centerfold |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HGMEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA41#v=onepage&q&f=false |journal=The Advocate |publisher=Sam Watters |volume= |issue=663 |pages=41–48 |doi= |accessdate=September 24, 2014}}</ref> By the time she was interviewed in 1999 for [[AIDS Project Los Angeles]] she identified as bisexual and said she had been infected at 16 "to the best of my knowledge."<ref name=Forrest1999>{{cite web |last=Forrest |first=Susan |date=November 1999 |title=A Bunny's Life |url=http://www.thebody.com/apla/nov99/bunny.html |website=thebody.com |publisher=Remedy Health Media |accessdate=}}</ref> A University of Toledo events notice in 2004 said that ''Playboy'' founder [[Hugh Hefner]] and the Playboy Foundation assisted Armstrong financially on her AIDS-awareness campaign, the College Campus Safer Sex education program.<ref name=Strunk041129>{{cite web |last=Strunk |first=Jon |date=November 29, 2004 |title=HIV-Infected Playboy Playmate to Speak With UT Students About Safe Sex |url=http://utnews.utoledo.edu/publish/Events_4/HIV-Infected_Playboy_Playmate_to_Speak_With_UT_Stu_1739.shtml |type=Event calendar |website=|publisher=University of Toledo |accessdate=September 24, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304023240/http://utnews.utoledo.edu/publish/Events_4/HIV-Infected_Playboy_Playmate_to_Speak_With_UT_Stu_1739.shtml |archivedate=March 4, 2016 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>
In a 2013 speech to community college students in [[Spokane, Washington|Spokane]], Washington, Armstrong shared details about the early days of her illness, the aggressive [[Zidovudine|AZT]] treatment that she endured, the good and bad times of that five-year period, and about her suicide attempt followed by a coma and a lengthy hospital stay.<ref name=Rogers131029>{{cite news |last=Rogers |first=Adrian |date=October 29, 2013 |title=Former model, Playboy playmate raises HIV awareness |url=http://www.spokesman.com/stories/2013/oct/29/former-model-playboy-playmate-raises-hiv-awareness/ |newspaper=Spokesman-Review |location=Spokane, Washington |accessdate=September 24, 2014}} </ref>
In addition to her former career as a model and her current activism, Armstrong has also competed as a bodybuilder.<ref>{{cite web |date=September 19, 2008 |title=Rebekka Armstrong featured in Leadership Workshop Series Sept. 23 |url=http://www.ulm.edu/news/archives/2008/sept08/rebekka_armstrong.html |publisher=The University of Louisiana at Monroe |accessdate=June 13, 2014}}</ref>
==Bodybuilding contest history== * 2004 Muscle Beach (Venice Beach, CA) – 1st (LW & Overall) * 2004 NPC Los Angeles Championship – 1st (MW) * 2005 NPC Pittsburgh – 1st (MW & Overall) * 2005 NPC Nationals – 12th (HW)<ref>{{cite web |last=Braun |first=Lori |date=November 18, 2010 |title=Rebekka Armstrong Gallery |url=http://femalemuscle.com/tag/rebekka-armstrong/ |website=femalemuscle.com |publisher=FemaleMuscle |accessdate=September 24, 2014}}</ref> * 2009 NPC Los Angeles Championships - 1st (HW and overall) * 2009 NPC USA Championships - 7th (LHW){{citation needed|date=September 2014}}
